reviewText: My son loves the Best of All About John Deere video his oma got him, but he was pretty disinterested in this one. It was interesting and cute, but it didn't capture his attention the way the other video did.

Rented this for my 3 1/2 yr old son, who is obsessed with all things John Deere right now. He loves it. He's trying to memorize the songs and watches it as many times as we will let him. If your kid likes tractors and farms, this is a no brainer.
Very good video it shows everything farmers use to get land ready and harvest thanks tommy a.

I asked my 5 year old why he like it and this was his response: "It's super cool because it has tractors in it, and it has a 1943 tractor in it!  There is a cool moving tractor that can lift up and it will only take 2 seconds to build it."
Our grandson and my husband like the John Deer Farm Days series.  It is great for kids who like to watch the big equipment work.
wonderful,  my 4 year old grandson is looking forward to the next Farm Days made,  the sooner the better for all!
One of my son's favorite, he got this video as a gift when he was 2.  He still watches it now that he is 4, had to buy the digital version since the DVD was so scratched it no longer would play.
Cute book. Love the board book.
My four year old loves this!

I should have been more aware of the content of this video.  I expected to see John Deere tractors at work as a learning tool for my 5 year old, but the farm equipment seen was little to none; it's all about bees, horses, and apples.  I can see a 2-3 year old liking this and relating to the cheesy songs, but not above that age group.
